riel   it was in use in the heart of England in the Middle Ages. The surname <i>Merrill</i> is derived from it. As <i>Muriel</i> it was at first used mainly in Scotland, but became more widely popular during the first half of the 20th century. Since then it has fallen from favour again."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":55,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":64,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Muriel de Lucy was born in 1160, in Staffordshire, England. She married Miles de Somery. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died in 1242, at the age of 82."},"et":{"1160–1242":"1160–1242","1171–1229":"1171–1229","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1195–Female":"1195–Surnud","1197–Male":"1197–Surnud","1199–Male":"1199–Surnud","1190":"1190","1242":"1242","1197":"1197","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","1171":"1171","ABT 1195":"umbes 1195","1215":"1215","ABT 1197":"umbes 1197","1224":"1224","ABT 1199":"umbes 1199","1199":"1199","1229":"1229","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England",", NORTHAMPTONSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1160–1242":"1160–1242","1171–1229":"1171–1229","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1195–Female":"1195–Kuollut","119